===Etymology===
1490, from {{etyl|frm}} {{term|mignon||lover, royal favourite, darling}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|mignot||dainty, pleasing, gentle, kind|lang=fro}}, of {{etyl|gem}} origin, from {{etyl|frk}} *{{term||minnjo|love, friendship, affection, memory|lang=frk}} from {{proto|Germanic|minþiō, mindiō|affectionate thought, care|lang=en}} from {{proto|Indo-European|men-, *mnā-|to think|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{goh}} {{term|minnja||love, care, affection, desire, memory|lang=goh}}, {{osx}} {{term|minnea||love|lang=osx}}. More at {{l|en|mind}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈmɪnjən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[loyal]] [[servant]] of another, usually more [[powerful]] being.
